io.sphere.sdk.customobjects.queries

Interface CustomObjectQuery<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the value of this custom object.
    All Superinterfaces:
    ExpansionPathContainer<CustomObject<T>>, MetaModelExpansionDsl<CustomObject<T>,CustomObjectQuery<T>,CustomObjectExpansionModel<CustomObject<T>>>, MetaModelQueryDsl<CustomObject<T>,CustomObjectQuery<T>,CustomObjectQueryModel<CustomObject<T>>,CustomObjectExpansionModel<CustomObject<T>>>, Query<CustomObject<T>>, QueryDsl<CustomObject<T>,CustomObjectQuery<T>>, ReferenceExpansionDsl<CustomObject<T>,CustomObjectQuery<T>>, ReferenceExpansionSupport<CustomObject<T>>, ResourceQuery<CustomObject<T>>, SphereRequest<PagedQueryResult<CustomObject<T>>>

    public interface CustomObjectQuery<T>
extends MetaModelQueryDsl<CustomObject<T>,CustomObjectQuery<T>,CustomObjectQueryModel<CustomObject<T>>,CustomObjectExpansionModel<CustomObject<T>>>

    Queries custom objects.

    withCustomObject(client(), "containerA", "key", customObjectA ->
    withCustomObject(client(), "containerB", "key", customObjectB -> {
        final Class<Foo> classForTheValue = Foo.class;
        final PagedQueryResult<CustomObject<Foo>> result =
                client().executeBlocking(CustomObjectQuery.of(classForTheValue).byContainer("containerA"));
        final List<CustomObject<Foo>> results = result.getResults();
        assertThat(results)
                .contains(customObjectA)
                .doesNotContain(customObjectB);
    })
);

    See the test code.
